1
00:00:09,100 --> 00:00:12,900
<i>One possibility that we need to
rule out immediately</i>

2
00:00:13,033 --> 00:00:15,333
<i> is acute myeloid leukemia.</i>

3
00:00:15,467 --> 00:00:16,967
<i> My child could have cancer?</i>

4
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:19,667
<i>Take advantage of the fact that
Jasmine's in the hospital</i>

5
00:00:19,800 --> 00:00:22,267
<i>so you can get closer
to your grandparents.</i>

6
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:23,500
<i>There's an emergency
at the office.</i>

7
00:00:23,633 --> 00:00:25,333
<i> Paolo, your daughter is sick.</i>

8
00:00:25,467 --> 00:00:28,600
<i>Let Marj take care of the things
at the hospital.</i>

9
00:00:28,733 --> 00:00:29,900
<i> She's the mother.</i>

10
00:00:30,133 --> 00:00:31,033
<i> That's where she belongs.</i>

11
00:00:31,167 --> 00:00:33,400
<i>You focus on the company
problem.</i>

12
00:00:34,167 --> 00:00:35,733
<i>You have to be realistic, Paolo.</i>

13
00:00:35,867 --> 00:00:37,667
<i>If our business were
to collapse,</i>

14
00:00:37,800 --> 00:00:39,567
<i>how would we be able to pay for
your daughter's treatment?</i>

15
00:00:39,700 --> 00:00:41,433
<i> Are you satisfied with this?</i>

16
00:00:41,567 --> 00:00:43,667
<i>Fine, I'll figure
something out again</i>

17
00:00:43,800 --> 00:00:45,867
<i>so we won't be a burden
in this house anymore.</i>

18
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:49,500
<i>Based on the blood test
and the bone marrow aspiration,</i>

19
00:00:49,633 --> 00:00:53,167
<i>Jasmine does have
acute myeloid leukemia.</i>

20
00:00:53,300 --> 00:00:54,633
<i> Marj, Marj!</i>

21
00:00:54,767 --> 00:00:55,833
<i> Marj.</i>

22
00:01:03,633 --> 00:01:04,600
Marj.

23
00:01:05,600 --> 00:01:07,300
How are you feeling?

24
00:01:07,467 --> 00:01:09,700
Where's Dr. Alvarez?

25
00:01:11,100 --> 00:01:12,067
He already left.

26
00:01:13,833 --> 00:01:15,800
But they explained
everything to me.

27
00:01:18,133 --> 00:01:20,900
They're going to start
the chemotherapy...

28
00:01:21,033 --> 00:01:22,267
of our daughter.

29
00:01:23,733 --> 00:01:25,533
The thing is...

30
00:01:25,667 --> 00:01:28,100
her immune system
will get even weaker.

31
00:01:29,733 --> 00:01:31,800
How are we going to tell her?

32
00:01:33,667 --> 00:01:35,033
We'll tell her the truth.

33
00:01:36,333 --> 00:01:37,967
We don't have a choice.

34
00:01:38,900 --> 00:01:42,967
She needs to know so she can
prepare herself mentally...

35
00:01:44,533 --> 00:01:46,167
because it won't be easy
for her.

36
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:51,867
Love, she might get scared.

37
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:54,000
She might lose hope.

38
00:01:55,967 --> 00:01:57,233
Marj, come on.

39
00:01:58,333 --> 00:02:00,533
You really think
she won't know eventually?

40
00:02:01,467 --> 00:02:02,500
Huh?

41
00:02:03,233 --> 00:02:04,267
Besides...

42
00:02:05,800 --> 00:02:07,900
if we lie to her...

43
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:10,033
and she finds out...

44
00:02:12,700 --> 00:02:14,500
it'll hurt her even more.

45
00:02:17,167 --> 00:02:18,733
And she'll lose trust in us.

46
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:22,067
Do you want that?

47
00:02:28,133 --> 00:02:30,767
Love, I don't know
what to do anymore.

48
00:02:31,767 --> 00:02:33,200
I'm scared.

49
00:02:33,333 --> 00:02:35,500
I don't know how to protect her

50
00:02:35,633 --> 00:02:38,900
from the pain and suffering
that she will go through.

51
00:02:39,033 --> 00:02:41,000
I don't know what to do.

52
00:02:42,700 --> 00:02:45,100
I can't do this alone.

53
00:02:46,067 --> 00:02:47,467
I need you now.

54
00:02:47,633 --> 00:02:49,333
I need you more than ever.

55
00:02:49,467 --> 00:02:50,667
Please don't leave me.

56
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:52,067
I can't do this without you.

57
00:03:10,367 --> 00:03:11,933
Why aren't you answering it?

58
00:03:13,133 --> 00:03:15,067
No one important.

59
00:04:07,700 --> 00:04:08,767
Darn it!

60
00:04:08,900 --> 00:04:10,400
He's still not answering
my calls!

61
00:04:11,433 --> 00:04:13,733
That probably means he's busy,

62
00:04:13,867 --> 00:04:15,300
or he just doesn't want to talk
to you.

63
00:04:16,400 --> 00:04:18,700
But it's work-related.

64
00:04:18,833 --> 00:04:20,367
I need a job.

65
00:04:21,167 --> 00:04:24,033
I sent him my application
three days ago,

66
00:04:24,167 --> 00:04:25,500
and he's just ignoring it.

67
00:04:25,633 --> 00:04:27,100
You really think he's going
to prioritize you?

68
00:04:27,733 --> 00:04:29,900
Isn't his daughter sick?

69
00:04:30,033 --> 00:04:31,400
So what?

70
00:04:31,533 --> 00:04:33,267
He has a daughter with me, too.

71
00:04:34,400 --> 00:04:36,433
I'm doing this for Ashley.

72
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:39,400
He can't just ignore me
like that.

73
00:04:45,733 --> 00:04:48,667
<i>I will not allow you
to treat me this way.</i>

74
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:51,667
<i>You can't avoid me
and ignore me forever.</i>

75
00:04:56,467 --> 00:05:00,033
I'll make sure he has no choice
but to face me.

76
00:05:01,067 --> 00:05:02,833
What are you planning to do?

77
00:05:08,667 --> 00:05:10,267
Hi Jasmine, I'm just going
to explain the procedure

78
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:11,433
we're going to do.

79
00:05:11,567 --> 00:05:14,333
The chemo will kill
the abnormal cells

80
00:05:14,467 --> 00:05:16,333
so your bone marrow

81
00:05:16,467 --> 00:05:20,367
can start producing healthy
blood cells again.

82
00:05:27,467 --> 00:05:28,967
Will it hurt?

83
00:05:29,100 --> 00:05:30,933
Well, there will be days when
you'll feel very tired,

84
00:05:31,067 --> 00:05:32,167
and you might throw up.

85
00:05:32,300 --> 00:05:35,100
But we have medication to manage
the side effects.

86
00:05:37,133 --> 00:05:39,033
Can I still go to school?

87
00:05:39,933 --> 00:05:44,000
We'll talk to your school
principal, sweetheart.

88
00:05:44,133 --> 00:05:50,267
Maybe you can do homeschooling
for now, or take a year off.

89
00:05:56,667 --> 00:05:58,200
- Pao.
- Oh?

90
00:05:58,333 --> 00:05:59,833
Can that wait until later?

91
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:01,933
Sorry.

92
00:06:02,067 --> 00:06:03,467
I agree with your mom.

93
00:06:03,833 --> 00:06:06,300
Right now, your recovery has
to be our top priority.

94
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:12,200
Your dad and I will never leave
you, Jasmine.

95
00:06:13,333 --> 00:06:16,267
You won't be alone through this.

96
00:06:17,467 --> 00:06:18,200
I promise, sweetheart.

97
00:06:18,333 --> 00:06:20,600
Your dad and I will be
right here.

98
00:06:44,533 --> 00:06:46,100
I want you to gather
all the information

99
00:06:46,233 --> 00:06:47,967
you can find about Mr. Lorenzo.

100
00:06:48,100 --> 00:06:49,433
The places he's tagged in,

101
00:06:49,567 --> 00:06:51,667
the big shots he hangs out with.

102
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:54,567
And check his social media, too.

103
00:06:54,700 --> 00:06:57,000
So we know how to approach him.

104
00:06:58,367 --> 00:06:59,433
Yes, Sir. Noted.

105
00:07:02,533 --> 00:07:04,233
Sir, please excuse me.

106
00:07:10,633 --> 00:07:12,133
I need to talk to you.

107
00:07:12,833 --> 00:07:14,167
What do you want?

108
00:07:14,933 --> 00:07:17,100
You're bothering me even here!

109
00:07:17,233 --> 00:07:19,833
If you had just answered
my calls and emails,

110
00:07:19,967 --> 00:07:21,767
we wouldn't be
in this situation.

111
00:07:21,900 --> 00:07:23,567
You wouldn't even have to ask.

112
00:07:23,700 --> 00:07:24,600
It's not like you don't know

113
00:07:24,733 --> 00:07:26,733
what's going on with my family
right now.

114
00:07:26,867 --> 00:07:28,700
You know Jasmine
is seriously ill.

115
00:07:29,267 --> 00:07:30,867
There are problems
with the company.

116
00:07:31,767 --> 00:07:33,367
I don't have time
for your silly games.

117
00:07:34,667 --> 00:07:36,967
Paolo, I'm not playing games.

118
00:07:38,967 --> 00:07:40,167
I just want one simple thing.

119
00:07:42,167 --> 00:07:43,200
A job.

120
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:47,100
Let me go back
into Torrecampo Realty.

121
00:07:48,867 --> 00:07:50,967
Don't tell me what I should
or shouldn't do!

122
00:07:52,867 --> 00:07:54,967
I'm sick of seeing you
in my house!

123
00:07:55,100 --> 00:07:56,667
And now I have
to see you here, too?

124
00:07:57,367 --> 00:07:59,100
Go find a job somewhere else.

125
00:07:59,233 --> 00:08:00,767
Because even if you beg me...

126
00:08:01,867 --> 00:08:03,300
I'm not taking you back here.

127
00:08:08,033 --> 00:08:09,067
So please?

128
00:08:09,200 --> 00:08:10,133
if you have nothing else to say,

129
00:08:10,267 --> 00:08:11,833
just leave.

130
00:08:11,967 --> 00:08:13,433
Wow!

131
00:08:13,567 --> 00:08:16,067
You're really that
self-absorbed.

132
00:08:16,200 --> 00:08:19,900
You won't even ask
why I need a job?

133
00:08:22,300 --> 00:08:23,767
This is for Ashley.

134
00:08:24,567 --> 00:08:29,100
I need to work because I can't
rely on your useless brother!

135
00:08:30,367 --> 00:08:32,733
If anything,
you should be happy.

136
00:08:33,267 --> 00:08:34,833
I'm actually trying
to stand on my own

137
00:08:34,967 --> 00:08:36,967
instead of depending on Edward.

138
00:08:37,733 --> 00:08:39,700
And yet you're still driving me
away like this?

139
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:46,000
Paolo, I'm working hard for our
daughter.

140
00:08:46,833 --> 00:08:48,733
Shut up!
Someone might hear you.

141
00:08:49,833 --> 00:08:52,733
Why is it always Jasmine you
care about?

142
00:08:53,900 --> 00:08:55,133
What about Ashley?

143
00:08:55,300 --> 00:08:56,667
She's your daughter, too!

144
00:08:57,933 --> 00:09:00,000
- I said shut up!
- No!

145
00:09:00,133 --> 00:09:01,667
I won't shut up!

146
00:09:04,300 --> 00:09:07,933
I'll tell everyone here

147
00:09:08,067 --> 00:09:09,167
that Ashley is your daughter

148
00:09:09,300 --> 00:09:12,500
if you don't give me
what I want.

149
00:09:14,667 --> 00:09:15,967
Your choice.

150
00:09:23,133 --> 00:09:25,167
You think I'm scared of you?

151
00:09:25,300 --> 00:09:26,267
Fine.

152
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:28,300
Go ahead.

153
00:09:29,833 --> 00:09:30,933
Go ahead.

154
00:09:31,067 --> 00:09:32,167
Spread it around.

155
00:09:33,667 --> 00:09:35,700
You think I'm the only one
who'll be ruined?

156
00:09:35,833 --> 00:09:36,800
You will too!

157
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:39,967
You're really pushing me, aren't
you?

158
00:09:40,733 --> 00:09:42,667
Maybe you forgot.

159
00:09:42,800 --> 00:09:44,300
Dad only accepted you

160
00:09:44,433 --> 00:09:47,867
because you agreed
to keep our secret.

161
00:09:48,500 --> 00:09:50,433
We kept this from Edward.

162
00:09:51,033 --> 00:09:52,300
He knows nothing.

163
00:09:52,933 --> 00:09:56,000
That's why he offered to marry
you in the first place.

164
00:09:56,133 --> 00:09:57,967
That's how you became
a Torrecampo, right?

165
00:09:58,533 --> 00:10:01,967
The name you're so proud to
flaunt to everyone you meet.

166
00:10:04,800 --> 00:10:07,100
If you expose us...

167
00:10:07,233 --> 00:10:08,967
Marj will hate me.

168
00:10:09,100 --> 00:10:10,767
It will destroy my family.

169
00:10:12,133 --> 00:10:14,400
But I'll still be a Torrecampo.

170
00:10:15,500 --> 00:10:17,267
How about you...

171
00:10:17,400 --> 00:10:20,500
on the other hand, where do you
think you'll end up?

172
00:10:23,233 --> 00:10:25,867
You think once
Edward finds out...

173
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:27,100
he won't leave you?

174
00:10:28,733 --> 00:10:30,767
And Ashley...

175
00:10:30,900 --> 00:10:33,200
do you really think
she'll forgive you

176
00:10:33,333 --> 00:10:35,433
for lying about her true
identity?

177
00:10:37,900 --> 00:10:40,800
Thea, you have a lot more to
lose.

178
00:10:43,400 --> 00:10:45,733
You'll lose your family.

179
00:10:45,867 --> 00:10:48,000
And your ambitions.

180
00:10:48,133 --> 00:10:50,100
Your status as a Torrecampo.

181
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:53,733
Everything you have right now.

182
00:11:06,433 --> 00:11:08,533
Don't think you've won, Paolo.

183
00:11:11,133 --> 00:11:12,933
You know me.

184
00:11:13,067 --> 00:11:14,167
I'm a fighter.

185
00:11:16,067 --> 00:11:18,433
Giving up isn't
in my vocabulary.

186
00:11:22,067 --> 00:11:24,033
So this conversation isn't over.

187
00:11:25,633 --> 00:11:28,900
I'll make sure
that when I come back...

188
00:11:30,100 --> 00:11:32,267
I'll get what I want.

189
00:12:12,100 --> 00:12:13,200
Excuse, Ma'am.

190
00:12:17,967 --> 00:12:22,033
Mom, where's Dad?

191
00:12:24,533 --> 00:12:27,333
Ah, your dad had to step out
for a while.

192
00:12:27,833 --> 00:12:29,300
He has some work.

193
00:12:30,167 --> 00:12:33,067
But Mommy's here if you need
anything, baby.

194
00:12:38,567 --> 00:12:41,167
There's really just one thing
I want, Mom.

195
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:45,667
I just want to be normal.

196
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:47,067
Like other kids.

197
00:12:48,933 --> 00:12:51,667
Not stuck here in the hospital.

198
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:56,667
Doing whatever I want.

199
00:13:00,667 --> 00:13:02,433
Close your eyes, baby.

200
00:13:03,300 --> 00:13:04,433
What?

201
00:13:04,967 --> 00:13:06,000
Come on, Jas.

202
00:13:06,133 --> 00:13:09,667
Close your eyes and just listen
to my voice.

203
00:13:10,767 --> 00:13:14,433
Close your eyes
and just listen to my voice.

204
00:13:18,167 --> 00:13:19,733
Just imagine...

205
00:13:20,900 --> 00:13:25,800
Two years from now, you're all
better.

206
00:13:28,133 --> 00:13:30,133
You've beaten your illness.

207
00:13:31,800 --> 00:13:35,667
You will turn 18,
it'll be your debut.

208
00:13:37,133 --> 00:13:40,800
You're... You're gonna be
dressed like a princess.

209
00:13:41,700 --> 00:13:43,767
You look so beautiful
and healthy

210
00:13:43,900 --> 00:13:46,867
and everyone will be amazed
by you.

211
00:13:47,800 --> 00:13:51,900
All you'll see are smiles
on people's faces.

212
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:55,967
No one will be sad.

213
00:13:57,300 --> 00:13:59,033
No one will be crying.

214
00:14:06,200 --> 00:14:08,867
Thank you, Mom.

215
00:14:34,967 --> 00:14:36,067
Sir Paolo.

216
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:39,000
Ah, here, let me help you bring
the flowers and cake inside.

217
00:14:44,367 --> 00:14:47,633
Jasmine isn't allowed
to have fresh flowers.

218
00:14:47,767 --> 00:14:49,300
They might carry bacteria
or fungi.

219
00:14:49,433 --> 00:14:52,100
There's a high risk of
infection.

220
00:14:52,467 --> 00:14:53,667
I'm sorry.

221
00:14:55,433 --> 00:14:56,433
Ganun ba?

222
00:14:57,033 --> 00:14:58,467
All right, sorry about that.

223
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:08,933
I don't know, Oscar.

224
00:15:10,433 --> 00:15:14,967
It feels like everything I do
is wrong.

225
00:15:17,167 --> 00:15:19,233
Like I can't do
anything right anymore.

226
00:15:21,700 --> 00:15:23,967
Sir Paolo,
please don't lose heart.

227
00:15:25,067 --> 00:15:28,800
In time, you'll learn
what you should

228
00:15:28,933 --> 00:15:30,300
and shouldn't do.

229
00:15:32,133 --> 00:15:35,567
But Oscar...
I'm Jasmine's father.

230
00:15:37,900 --> 00:15:39,000
From the start,

231
00:15:39,133 --> 00:15:41,167
I should already know the right
thing to do as Marj does.

232
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:46,867
How am I supposed to protect
and save my daughter

233
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:48,533
if I keep messing everything up?

234
00:15:58,933 --> 00:16:00,667
- Where's Yolly?
- She's over there, Sir.

235
00:16:00,800 --> 00:16:02,967
- Mom.
- Paolo, why are you here?

236
00:16:03,100 --> 00:16:05,600
I just had Yolly prepare some
documents for me.

237
00:16:05,733 --> 00:16:07,033
I have a meeting nearby.

238
00:16:08,167 --> 00:16:10,233
Aren't you supposed to be
at the hospital?

239
00:16:11,667 --> 00:16:13,300
Marj is there.

240
00:16:13,433 --> 00:16:15,867
Dad and I are still dealing
with that problem

241
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:17,400
with Mr. Lorenzo, right?

242
00:16:18,800 --> 00:16:21,033
What if Jasmine looks for you?

243
00:16:21,167 --> 00:16:23,033
She might get upset.

244
00:16:28,533 --> 00:16:29,700
Mom...

245
00:16:35,200 --> 00:16:37,000
When Edward and I were kids...

246
00:16:40,033 --> 00:16:41,100
it was you.

247
00:16:42,200 --> 00:16:43,700
Was always there for us.

248
00:16:44,967 --> 00:16:47,967
Dad was always at work.

249
00:16:48,533 --> 00:16:50,033
Always with clients.

250
00:16:51,600 --> 00:16:53,000
I'm always looking for him...

251
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:55,200
even Edward.

252
00:16:56,967 --> 00:16:58,700
I really felt sorry for you
back then.

253
00:16:59,600 --> 00:17:00,433
Especially for Edward,

254
00:17:00,567 --> 00:17:02,133
since he was sick
a lot as a kid.

255
00:17:03,433 --> 00:17:06,167
And Jasmine's situation
is even worse.

256
00:17:06,300 --> 00:17:08,100
Her condition is more serious.

257
00:17:08,500 --> 00:17:09,933
And she's a girl.

258
00:17:10,067 --> 00:17:13,033
I'm sure she would want
her father next to her.

259
00:17:15,700 --> 00:17:16,800
I know.

260
00:17:18,433 --> 00:17:22,200
But remember, over time,

261
00:17:22,333 --> 00:17:24,167
Edward and I understood.

262
00:17:25,267 --> 00:17:28,867
Dad couldn't always visit us
at the hospital...

263
00:17:30,167 --> 00:17:31,467
because he had to work.

264
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:35,967
So he could provide
all of our needs.

265
00:17:37,533 --> 00:17:40,033
That's no different
from what I'm doing now.

266
00:17:42,233 --> 00:17:46,900
I want to focus on solving
the problem of our company...

267
00:17:48,433 --> 00:17:49,967
so it doesn't collapse.

268
00:17:53,100 --> 00:17:55,133
So we can afford Jasmine's
treatment.

269
00:17:58,467 --> 00:17:59,900
Marj is enough for Jas.

270
00:18:01,300 --> 00:18:02,600
Just like...

271
00:18:03,867 --> 00:18:07,267
how you were enough
for Edward and me.

272
00:18:08,767 --> 00:18:11,767
I acted strong in front of you
back then.

273
00:18:13,067 --> 00:18:17,000
I endured it because
that's what mothers do.

274
00:18:18,900 --> 00:18:21,633
But it didn't mean
that I didn't wish

275
00:18:21,800 --> 00:18:23,900
your father was there
to help me.

276
00:18:27,067 --> 00:18:29,667
And I'm sure that's what Marj is
doing right now.

277
00:18:32,333 --> 00:18:34,033
I never cared much for her

278
00:18:34,167 --> 00:18:40,300
But now, as a mother,
I can relate to her.

279
00:18:45,700 --> 00:18:48,033
If there's any problem,

280
00:18:48,167 --> 00:18:49,800
I'm sure Marj will give me
a call.

281
00:18:49,933 --> 00:18:50,967
Yes, of course.

282
00:18:51,967 --> 00:18:53,600
But for now, Mom,
I need to focus

283
00:18:53,733 --> 00:18:56,533
on finding a solution
for the company, okay?

284
00:18:56,700 --> 00:18:58,067
Okay.

285
00:19:07,167 --> 00:19:08,267
I have to go.

286
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:09,367
I still need to work.

287
00:19:09,500 --> 00:19:10,733
- Yes, I know.
- Thank you.

288
00:19:10,867 --> 00:19:12,700
- Okay.
- All right.

289
00:19:25,167 --> 00:19:30,033
If Paolo thinks I'm just going
to give up, he's mistaken.

290
00:19:30,533 --> 00:19:32,000
I'll try to find another way

291
00:19:32,133 --> 00:19:34,733
to convince him to let me back
into the company.

292
00:19:35,933 --> 00:19:39,533
But why are you so desperate to
get back into Torrecampo Realty?

293
00:19:39,667 --> 00:19:42,300
What? So you can be close
to Paolo?

294
00:19:42,933 --> 00:19:43,967
Wait a minute.

295
00:19:44,600 --> 00:19:46,867
Do you still have a thing
for Paolo?

296
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:49,667
That's not it, Lalaine.

297
00:19:51,900 --> 00:19:53,033
Then what?

298
00:19:55,133 --> 00:19:57,167
You know my husband
is basically an outcast

299
00:19:57,300 --> 00:19:59,033
in his own family, right?

300
00:19:59,167 --> 00:20:03,467
His father will never accept him
after all his screw-ups.

301
00:20:03,633 --> 00:20:06,700
So someone has to carry
our family's name.

302
00:20:06,833 --> 00:20:09,667
I need to get
into Torrecampo Realty

303
00:20:09,800 --> 00:20:13,433
to prove myself to Daddy Greg
and Mama Regina.

304
00:20:17,600 --> 00:20:19,700
Wow, you're really
going all out.

305
00:20:19,833 --> 00:20:21,633
Well, we don't really have
a choice.

306
00:20:22,100 --> 00:20:24,000
We need to clean up
our reputation

307
00:20:24,133 --> 00:20:25,833
with Greg Torrecampo,

308
00:20:25,967 --> 00:20:27,200
so someday...

309
00:20:27,333 --> 00:20:30,667
we won't be at a disadvantage
when it comes to his last will.

310
00:20:32,967 --> 00:20:36,000
But what if Paolo really doesn't
want you back at work?

311
00:20:36,167 --> 00:20:40,133
Especially now that he's in
charge of the whole company.

312
00:20:42,567 --> 00:20:44,100
There has to be another way.

313
00:21:00,767 --> 00:21:02,967
Stephen Lorenzo?

314
00:21:10,933 --> 00:21:12,300
<i>- Come in.
- Stephen, my friend.</i>

315
00:21:12,433 --> 00:21:13,667
<i> Have you been waiting long?</i>

316
00:21:13,800 --> 00:21:14,833
<i> No, it's fine.</i>

317
00:21:16,667 --> 00:21:17,667
<i> Sorry about that.</i>

318
00:21:18,167 --> 00:21:20,667
<i>Thea took a while getting
herself all dressed up</i>

319
00:21:20,800 --> 00:21:23,167
<i>so we wouldn't embarrass
ourselves in front of you.</i>

320
00:21:25,667 --> 00:21:27,200
<i> They were right, Manuel.</i>

321
00:21:27,900 --> 00:21:29,700
<i> Your daughter is beautiful.</i>

322
00:21:31,967 --> 00:21:34,167
<i> She really looks stunning.</i>

323
00:21:35,400 --> 00:21:36,967
<i>Because of that,
you get a bonus.</i>

324
00:21:38,567 --> 00:21:40,033
<i> Thanks, my friend.</i>

325
00:21:41,800 --> 00:21:43,100
<i> I'll leave Thea to you.</i>

326
00:21:43,233 --> 00:21:44,833
<i> She's a very obedient girl.</i>

327
00:21:44,967 --> 00:21:48,233
<i>So I'm sure you won't have any
problems with her.</i>

328
00:21:48,367 --> 00:21:49,800
<i>- Good.
- Oh, Thea,</i>

329
00:21:49,933 --> 00:21:52,800
<i>make sure you don't give
Mr. Lorenzo a headache, okay?</i>

330
00:22:05,667 --> 00:22:06,933
<i> Let's take a picture.</i>

331
00:22:15,367 --> 00:22:17,833
<i> Hey, smile.</i>

332
00:22:26,300 --> 00:22:27,633
<i> Oh.</i>

333
00:22:27,767 --> 00:22:29,167
<i> Look over here.</i>

334
00:22:30,167 --> 00:22:31,400
<i> You look gorgeous.</i>

335
00:22:31,967 --> 00:22:33,033
<i> Smile.</i>

336
00:22:40,567 --> 00:22:46,033
I think I know how I can get
back into Torrecampo Realty.

337
00:22:47,833 --> 00:22:51,200
And I'm sure Paolo won't be able
to say no to me this time.

338
00:23:11,533 --> 00:23:13,500
Hi, Mr. Lorenzo.

339
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:20,400
Good to know this is still
your favorite restaurant.

340
00:23:23,533 --> 00:23:26,000
Is this still
where you bring the girls...

341
00:23:26,867 --> 00:23:28,600
after you've had your way
with them?

342
00:23:32,833 --> 00:23:34,633
Who the hell are you?

343
00:23:34,767 --> 00:23:35,800
Oh...

344
00:23:40,067 --> 00:23:41,733
You don't remember me?

345
00:23:43,600 --> 00:23:44,833
Gosh.

346
00:23:45,467 --> 00:23:48,800
were there really that many
underage girls...

347
00:23:52,233 --> 00:23:53,500
you victimized...

348
00:23:55,833 --> 00:23:58,033
that I didn't even leave
an impression...

349
00:24:02,567 --> 00:24:04,367
I have no idea
what you're talking about.

350
00:24:04,500 --> 00:24:05,700
Oh.

351
00:24:06,533 --> 00:24:07,833
Oh.

352
00:24:08,933 --> 00:24:10,700
Cut the crap, Mr. Lorenzo.

353
00:24:15,300 --> 00:24:16,567
It's me.

354
00:24:18,367 --> 00:24:19,467
Thea.

355
00:24:22,600 --> 00:24:23,933
<i> Don't be scared.</i>

356
00:24:25,267 --> 00:24:29,267
The daughter of your business
partner, Manuel Villareal.

357
00:24:30,400 --> 00:24:32,333
<i>Your daughter
is beautiful, Manuel.</i>

358
00:24:41,233 --> 00:24:42,500
Remember now?

359
00:24:45,767 --> 00:24:47,000
Oh.

360
00:24:49,733 --> 00:24:53,833
The underage girl that my father
used to pay off his debt to you.

361
00:25:06,867 --> 00:25:08,367
This is you, right?

362
00:25:13,833 --> 00:25:16,067
I knew it...

363
00:25:16,200 --> 00:25:18,867
this would come
in handy someday.

364
00:25:22,200 --> 00:25:23,533
And there's more.

365
00:25:24,500 --> 00:25:26,200
I even have backups online.

366
00:25:27,300 --> 00:25:28,900
So there's no way
you can erase...

367
00:25:29,767 --> 00:25:32,267
the disgusting thing
you did to me.

368
00:25:42,333 --> 00:25:43,633
Let me guess.

369
00:25:43,767 --> 00:25:45,300
You just came from the hospital
again, right?

370
00:25:45,433 --> 00:25:47,900
There's nothing wrong
with visiting Jasmine.

371
00:25:48,033 --> 00:25:51,533
Did you really visit Jasmine...
or Marj?

372
00:25:51,667 --> 00:25:52,567
Tell me the truth, Paolo.

373
00:25:52,700 --> 00:25:54,700
Do you actually care
about our daughter?

374
00:25:54,833 --> 00:25:57,900
Or am I really going to have to
fight this battle alone for her?

375
00:25:58,033 --> 00:25:59,633
Your choice, Mr. Lorenzo.

376
00:25:59,767 --> 00:26:01,900
You either do exactly
what I tell you,

377
00:26:02,033 --> 00:26:03,733
or you let your reputation

378
00:26:03,867 --> 00:26:07,067
and your company be destroyed.

379
00:26:07,200 --> 00:26:10,200
I'm doing everything
I'm supposed to do.

380
00:26:10,367 --> 00:26:13,100
But it's still not enough
for you!

381
00:26:13,233 --> 00:26:15,200
I don't even know
where I stand anymore.

382
00:26:15,567 --> 00:26:17,533
After everything I did today,

383
00:26:17,667 --> 00:26:20,567
they'll be the ones kneeling
and begging me.

384
00:26:20,700 --> 00:26:22,667
Face it, you need me, too.
